• Sol I: 1.6 g of ammonium molybdate \(\(NH4)6Mo7O244H2O; M.W.=1235.86) is dissolved in 12 mL water.





• Sol II: 4 mL concentrated HCl and 1.0 mL of mercury are shaken with 8 mL of Sol I for 60 min and filtered through glass wool.





• Sol III: 20 mL of concentrated H2SO4 is added to the remainder of Sol I, then, Sol II is added to the resultant solution to give Sol III.





• Chromagenic solution: 45 mL methanol, 5 mL chloroform, and 20 mL water are added to 25 mL Sol III. It is stable for 3 months at 5 C.





• CM mixture 2:1: chloroform: methanol w/BHT = 2 L: 1 L: 100 mg











• Mobile phase:


1. Use 1000 mL graduate cylinder to add 3 L of HPLC grade acetonitrile to a 4 L bottle;
  2. Use 100 mL graduate cylinder to add 150 mL of HPLC grade methanol to the 4 L bottle;
  3. Use 50 mL graduate cylinder to add 27 mL of HPLC \(or ACS) grade phosphoric acid to the 4 L bottle;
  4. Use 1000 µL automatic pipette to add 760 µL of to HPLC \(or ACS) grade 98% sulfuric acid to the 4 L bottle;
  5. Use stir bar to degas the mixture. Shake the bottle upside down vigorously several times.
  


• CM mixture:chloroform:methanol:butylated hydroxytolune \(BHT) = 2L:1L:100mg.





• CM mixture:chloroform:BHT= 100 mL:900 mL:100mg.
